# API Services and Data Fetching

## Weather API Integration
- Main API service: [src/services/weatherApi.ts](mdc:src/services/weatherApi.ts)
- Use proper TypeScript types from [src/types/weather.ts](mdc:src/types/weather.ts)
- Implement proper error handling for API failures
- Handle rate limiting and API key management

## Data Fetching Patterns
- Use React hooks for data fetching (useEffect, useState)
- Implement loading states and error handling
- Cache API responses when appropriate
- Use the custom hooks in [src/hooks/](mdc:src/hooks/) for reusable logic

## Environment Configuration
- API keys should be stored in environment variables
- Use [env.example](mdc:env.example) as a template for required environment variables
- Never commit API keys to version control

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use [src/components/ErrorMessage.tsx](mdc:src/components/ErrorMessage.tsx) for user-facing errors
- Log errors appropriately for debugging
- Provide fallback UI states for failed API calls